        h4 Background
        p When I built my first eCommerce website back in 2007, I started to glimpse the great importance of crafting effective experiences on the web. Countless times I would have an idea for a way to grow my business online and run into complications when I tried to implement them. Everything was much more difficult then it seemed. I was throwing time and money at my online business without a fundamental understanding of a digital marketing strategy let alone a website's role in the business.
        p The lessons I learned in the failures of multiple web projects were building into a skillset that had great value to other Entrepreneurs. I realized there were other entrepreneurs who had brilliant ideas, but had trouble implementing them just like I did.
        h4 Work
        p My consulting work involves turning ideas into reality. Using the tools of the web, I help my clients create digital strategies and implement those strategies into a website or a web application.
        p I've learned that the best way to approach a project is through a series of iterations. Once a project is launched, it is then tested to improve each key performance indicator identified in the project requirements. 
        p I often work under the principles of &ldquo;Fail early and fail often&rdquo; and &ldquo;If you can't measure it, you cannot improve it&rdquo;.
        h4 Expertise
        p The following are a list of the services I consider in my domain of expertise as a User Experience Designer:
        ul 
          li Brand strategy
          li Interaction design
          li Visual design
          li Interface design
          li Mobile-first web development
        h4 Competencies
        p Given my range of experience as an Entrepreneur on the web, I've acquired a long list of competencies which I can provide as is appropriate:
